Clarence Avant, known as "the Godfather of Black Music," was a legendary figure who brought people together and uplifted others throughout his career. He played a significant role in the music industry and the civil rights movement, mentoring and shaping the careers of numerous Black artists, athletes, and producers. Avant also supported community leaders during challenging times and facilitated opportunities for elected officials. He was described as generous, funny, and compassionate. The author expresses condolences to Avant's loved ones, including Nicole, Alex, and Ted.